These brownies are delicious! I made them yesterday to take to my mom's house on Mother's day and it's taken a lot of willpower not to eat the entire pan. I followed the recipe as written and they turned out beautifully. I took the advice of other reviewers and covered the pan with foil for the first 10 minutes of baking. I ended up baking them for a full 48 minutes instead of the 30-35 minutes indicated. At 30 minutes the centre was still jiggly. I put the foil back on the pan for the last 5 minutes as well just to protect the topping. The end result was a cakey/fudgey brownie with a perfect coconut topping. This one is a keeper.

