Another delicious, EZ, cocoa-powder brownie recipe. A bit more cakelike, but still fudgy & dense. (I'm a fan of all kinds of brownies, but I prefer a dense & gooey consistency over the cake-like versions.) Once again, I melted my butter in a pyrex mixing bowl, in the micro (what's with all the "dirtying" of saucepans, all you recipe writers?), then beat in the sugar, vanilla & eggs. Gee, all in a single bowl - what a concept! The topping, although delicious, created an element of mess that I would prefer to avoid in the future, esp when transporting the finished product to a party or picnic. So while I liked the flavor of both layers, I'll most likely forego the topping if I make these again. Unless of course I serve them as a dessert course at home, topped with vanilla ice cream or creme fraiche. Hmmmm ... now there's a good idea ...

